ld-asia-india-66862838.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20Send%20Troops%20To%20US-Mexico%20Border%20If%20Elected%20To%20Power%2C%20Says%20Trump%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%C2%A0Former%20U.S.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20if%20elected%20again%20he%20would%20shift%20resources%20from%20federal%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20and%20send%20thousands%20of%20overseas-based%20troops%20to%20the%20U.S.-Mexico%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20supporters%20in%20Iowa%2C%20where%20the%20Republican%20Party's%20first%20nominating%20contest%20for%20the%20November%202024%20election%20will%20be%20held%20in%20January%2C%20Trump%20also%20promised%20to%20expand%20on%20a%20travel%20ban%20that%20barred%20people%20from%20several%20countries%20with%20majority%20Muslim%20populations%20during%20his%202017-2021%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECalling%20record%20illegal%20U.S.-Mexico%20border%20crossings%20under%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20an%20%26quot%3Binvasion%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20sought%20to%20place%20blame%20for%20the%20problem%20on%20the%20current%20administration.%20Biden%2C%20a%20Democrat%2C%20is%20running%20for%20re-election%20and%20could%20have%20a%20rematch%20election%20against%20the%20Republican%20front-runner%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUpon%20my%20inauguration%20I%20will%20immediately%20terminate%20every%20open%20borders%20policy%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20at%20a%20rally%20in%20Dubuque.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20make%20clear%20that%20we%20must%20use%20any%20and%20all%20resources%20needed%20to%20stop%20the%20invasion%2C%20including%20moving%20thousands%20of%20troops%20currently%20stationed%20overseas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETrump%20provided%20few%20specifics%2C%20including%20on%20exactly%20how%20he%20planned%20to%20expand%20on%20any%20ban%20imposed%20on%20Muslim-majority%20countries.%20It%20was%20unclear%20if%20Trump%20would%20face%20any%20legal%20hurdles%20to%20implementing%20suc