021%20from%20cofounder%20Apoorva%20Mehta%20(right).%3Cp%3EInstacart%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInstacart%20shares%20slumped%2011%25%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFinance%20professor%C2%A0Aswath%20Damodaran%20posted%20a%20harsh%20analysis%20of%20the%20company's%20core%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECEO%20Fidji%20Simo%20built%20an%20impressive%20ads%20business%2C%20but%20the%20main%20grocery%20delivery%20operation%20is%20tough.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20have%20a%20healthy%20digital%20advertising%20business%2C%20you%20actually%20have%20to%20have%20something%20else%20substantial%20sitting%20behind%20it%2C%20luring%20customers%20to%20visit%20your%20site%20and%20hopefully%20spend%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20concerns%20that%20has%20turned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-founder-apoorva-mehta-ipo-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstacart's%20IPO%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20flop%20on%20its%20second%20day%20as%20a%20public%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stock%20slumped%2011%25%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20close%20at%20%2430.10%20per%20share%2C%20a%20whisker%20away%20from%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-ipo-billions-sequoia-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20%2430%20per%20share%3C%2Fa%3E%20listing%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20successful%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-ipo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIPO%3C%2Fa%3E%20must%20deliver%20a%20big%20pop%20to%20the%20investors%20who%20signed%20on%20to%20buy%20stock%20when%20it%20debuts.%20Gains%20of%2020%25%20or%20more%20are%20pretty%20solid.%20After%20an%20early%20surge%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Instacart%20has%20now%20delivered%20its%20new%20shareholders%20almost%20nothing%20in%202%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20valued%20at%20just%20over%20%248%20billion%2C%20down%20from%20%2439%20billion%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Several%20late-stage%20investors%2C%20including%20D1%2C%20Fidelity%2C%20DST%20Global%20and%20T.%20Rowe%20Price%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F09%2F15%2Fsequoia-andreessen-set-to-take-massive-hit-on-2021-instacart-investment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elikely%20sitting%20on%20losses%20now%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20from%20Aswath%20Damodaran%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20NYU's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20came%20out%20with%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faswathdamodaran.blogspot.com%2F2023%2F09%2Fputting-instacart-before-grocery-horse.html%3Fm%3D1%26s%3D09%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20Instacart's%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20valuing%20the%20company%20at%20%2429%20a%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%2C%20and%20its%20relatively%20new%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-ceo-fidji-simos-stock-worth-13-million-valuation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFidji%20Simo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20built%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-advertising-business-revenue-ipo-amazon-seth-dallaire-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpressive%20advertising%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20top%20of%20the%20company's%20core%20grocery%20delivery%20operation.%20That%20addition%20has%20generated%20new%20revenue%20and%20even%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20future%20growth%20of%20Instacart%20will%20ultimately%20depend%20on%20how%20many%20customers%20it%20has%20and%20how%20much%20they%20spend.%20Without%20that%2C%20there's%20no%20one%20to%20advertise%20to.%20So%20Damodaran%20rightly%20focused%20his%20analysis%20mostly%20on%20the%20grocery%20delivery%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20takeaway%20is%20that%20grocery%20delivery%20is%20a%20tough%20business.%20I%20pulled%20out%20some%20highlights%20from%20Damodaran's%20blog%20to%20illustrate%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20declined%20to%20comment%20about%20its%20share%20price%20decline%20and%20Damodaran's%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrocery%20is%20a%20low-margin%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart's%20take%20rate%20was%207.5%25%20over%20the%20past%2012%20months.%20That's%20much%20lower%20than%20Airbnb%20and%20Doordash%2C%20Damodaran%20wrote.%20The%20reason%3A%20The%20grocery%20business%20is%20low-margin%2C%20so%20there's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20room%20for%20Instacart%20to%20skim%20more%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20an%20intermediary%20in%20a%20business%20with%20slim%20operating%20margins%2C%20as%20Instacart%20is%2C%20the%20low%20operating%20profitability%20of%20the%20grocery%20business%20will%20limit%20how%20much%20you%20can%20claim%20as%20a%20price%20for%20intermediation%2C%20in%20service%20fees%2C%26quot%3B%20Damodaran%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMost%20people%20like%20to%20go%20to%20grocery%20stores%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20non-processed%20food%2C%20especially%20fresh%20meats%20and%20produce%2C%20being%20able%20to%20see%20and%20touch%20items%20before%20you%20buy%20them%20is%20part%20of%20the%20shopping%20experience.%20Online%20photos%20don't%20cut%20it.%20I%20personally%20like%20to%20feel%20the%20avocados%20before%20I%20buy%20them.%20And%20those%20endless%20product%20substitution%20messages%20from%20rushed%20Instacart%20Shoppers%20are%20infuriating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECOVID%20hangover%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20saw%20orders%20and%20revenue%20surge%20dramatically%20when%20everyone%20was%20stuck%20at%20home%20during%20COVID-19.%20Makes%20sense.%20But%20once%20the%20pandemic%20ebbed%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20consumers%20went%20back%20to%20their%20local%20grocery%20store%20(see%20the%20section%20above).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCaught%20up%20in%20the%20mood%20of%20the%20moment%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20so%20many%20extrapolated%20Instacart's%20success%20in%202020%20into%20the%20future%2C%20forecasting%20that%20the%20shift%20to%20online%20grocery%20shopping%20would%20be%20permanent%2C%20and%20that%20Instacart%20would%20dominate%20that%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Damodaran%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrowth%20is%20capped%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Instacart%20customers%20have%20stayed%20with%20the%20service%2C%20judging%20the%20convenience%20to%20be%20worth%20it%20over%20the%20downsides.%20However%2C%20the%20grocery%20industry%20is%20not%20a%20growth%20sector%2C%20unlike%20other%20parts%20of%20e-commerce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ceiling%20on%20online%20grocery%20retail%20will%20remain%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20ceiling%20on%20online%20shopping%20in%20other%20areas%20in%20retail%2C%20with%20even%20optimists%20capping%20the%20share%20at%2020%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Damodaran%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20short%2C%20the%20growth%20in%20online%20grocery%20sales%20will%20be%20higher%20than%20total%20grocery%20sales%20growth%2C%20but%20not%20overwhelmingly%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECompetition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20grocers%20woke%20up%20and%20started%20offering%20online%20shopping%20services%20directly%20to%20their%20own%20customers%2C%20often%20preferring%20to%20have%20consumers%20pick-up%20their%20orders%20rather%20than%20deliver%20them.%20These%20offerings%20are%20pretty%20cost%20competitive%20because%20most%20grocery%20stores%20nixed%20the%20extra%20service%20fees%20and%20used%20existing%20employees%20as%20shoppers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20is%20also%20starting%20to%20face%20competition%20from%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20and%20GrubHub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20short%2C%20Instacart%20will%20be%20lucky%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20its%20existing%20market%20share%2C%20even%20if%20it%20plays%20its%20cards%20right%2C%20leaving%20its%20growth%20at%20or%20below%20the%20growth%20in%20the%20overall%20online%20grocery%20shopping%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Damodaran%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECosts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20usually%20pays%20its%20Shoppers%20based%20on%20the%20number%20of%20orders%20they%20handle%20and%20how%20many%20deliveries%20they%20make.%20This%20is%20a%20major%20expense%20for%20the%20company%20and%20it%20is%20variable%2C%20rising%20and%20falling%20with%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20reduces%20risk%2C%20but%20it%20means%20Instacart%20can't%20benefit%20much%20from%20economies%20of%20scale.%20This%20is%20a%20core%20feature%20of%20most%20tech%20companies%20that%20investors%20love.%20As%20sales%20rise%2C%20expenses%20usually%20don't%20rise%20as%20much%20for%20a%20software%20company%2C%20which%20often%20means%20big%20profits%20over%20time.%20Instacart%20doesn't%20really%20have%20this%2C%20according%20to%20Damodaran.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrowth%20has%20slowed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20companies%20are%20expected%20to%20grow%20quickly.%20Instacart's%20core%20business%20isn't%20really%20doing%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20handled%20262.6%20million%20orders%20in%202022%20versus%20263.20%20million%20in%20the%20last%2012%20months.%20Gross%20transaction%20volume%20was%20%2428.8%20billion%20in%202022%20versus%20%2429.4%20billion%20in%20the%20past%2012%20months%2C%20according%20to%20Damodaran's%20blog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funderstanding-instacarts-ipo-flop-grocery-business-hard-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695247049000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650b5df512dc4f001a176d74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funderstanding-instacarts-ipo-flop-grocery-business-hard-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20analysis%20of%20Instacart's%20lackluster%20IPO%20performance%20and%20its%20tough%20grocery%20delivery%20business%20model.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUr