ia%20Foxx%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e65233912f290019a9d803%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESen.%20Bill%20Cassidy%20and%20Rep.%20Virginia%20Foxx.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Bill%20Clark%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ERep.%20Virginia%20Foxx%20and%20Sen.%20Bill%20Cassidy%20asked%20the%20GAO%20to%20investigate%20the%20student-loan%20payment%20resumption.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThey%20said%20they're%20concerned%20loan%20servicers%20are%20not%20adequately%20prepared%20to%20facilitate%20repayment.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EInterest%20started%20building%20on%20balances%20on%20September%201%2C%20and%20bills%20will%20start%20becoming%20due%20next%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20millions%20of%20student-loan%20borrowers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-payment-pause-is-over-interest-resuming-borrower-balances-2023-8%5C%22%3Eabout%20to%20enter%20an%20unprecedented%20transition%20back%20into%20repayment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20two%20leading%20Republican%20lawmakers%20are%20worried%20loan%20companies%20are%20not%20up%20to%20the%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Rep.%20Virginia%20Foxx%20and%20Sen.%20Bill%20Cassidy%20%E2%80%94%20top%20Republicans%20on%20the%20House%20and%20Senate%20education%20committees%2C%20respectively%20%E2%80%94%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.help.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Ffoxx_return_to_repayment_letter.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20requesting%20that%20it%20look%20into%20the%20Education%20Department's%20efforts%20to%20prepare%20for%20repayment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20student-loan%20payment%20pause%20officially%20ended%20on%20September%201%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-company-nelnet-call-center-website-down-debt-interest-2023-9%5C%22%3Einterest%20began%20accruing%20again%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20federal%20borrowers'%20balances%2C%20and%20bills%20will%20start%20becoming%20due%20next%20month.%20The%20Education%20Department%2C%20along%20with%20student-loan%20companies%2C%20have%20never%20managed%20a%20transition%20back%20into%20repayment%20at%20this%20scale%2C%20and%20Foxx%20and%20Cassidy%20said%20in%20their%20letter%20that%20they're%20concerned%20the%20necessary%20preparation%20is%20not%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudent%20loan%20servicers%20will%20be%20responsible%20for%20helping%20millions%20of%20borrowers%20return%20to%20repayment%2C%20yet%20it%20is%20unclear%20whether%20the%20Department%20has%20provided%20servicers%20with%20the%20necessary%20guidance%20and%20instruction%20they%20need%20to%20assist%20borrowers%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20(GAO)%20has%20found%20weaknesses%20in%20the%20Department's%20efforts%20to%20provide%20appropriate%20guidance%20and%20instructions%20to%20servicers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawmakers%20cited%20a%202018%20GAO%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fgao-18-547.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20found%20the%20Education%20Department%20did%20not%20provide%20%26quot%3Bkey%20information%26quot%3B%20regarding%20the%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%20program%20to%20servicers%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20borrowers%20being%20improperly%20denied%20or%20kept%20in%20repayment%20for%20longer%20than%20necessary.%20Additionally%2C%20Cassidy%20and%20Foxx%20said%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bunclear%20whether%20borrowers%20will%20begin%20repayments%20when%20billing%20statements%20resume.%20Given%20the%20multiple%20prior%20deadlines%20for%20the%20return%20to%20repayment%20and%20the%20repeated%20extensions%20of%20the%20payment%20pause%2C%20it%20is%20highly%20likely%20there%20will%20be%20confusion%20among%20borrowers%20and%20many%20who%20may%20not%20take%20this%20repayment%20deadline%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawmakers%20requested%20the%20GAO%20begin%20its%20investigation%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20giving%20the%20looming%20payment%20restart%20date%2C%20and%20the%20asked%20the%20agency%20to%20examine%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20guidance%20it%20has%20given%20to%20servicers%20surrounding%20repayment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Education%20Department%20spokesperson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-payments-resume-confusion-borrowers-debt-relief-biden-2023-8%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20department%20remains%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20servicers%20to%20ensure%20information%20is%20effectively%20reaching%20borrowers%20regarding%20the%20upcoming%20changes%20to%20the%20loan%20industry.%20That%20includes%20the%20new%20SAVE%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%2C%20intended%20to%20lower%20borrowers'%20monthly%20payments%2C%20along%20with%20a%2012-month%20%26quot%3Bon-ramp%26quot%3B%20period%20during%20which%20the%20department%20will%20not%20report%20missed%20payments%20to%20credit%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20borrowers%20have%20already%20encountered%20a%20range%20of%20challenges%20before%20their%20bills%20are%20due.%20One%20student-loan%20company%2C%20Nelnet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-company-website-call-center-shut-down-borrowers-payments-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehas%20shut%20down%20its%20call%20center%20and%20website%20multiple%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%20two%20months%20due%20to%20technical%20difficulties%2C%20leaving%20borrowers%20who%20need%20help%20with%20repayment%20in%20limbo.%20Additionally%2C%20some%20borrowers%20have%20told%20Insider%20their%20monthly%20statement%20is%20inaccurate%2C%20but%20long%20hold%20times%20with%20customer%20service%20have%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20get%20those%20issues%20resolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20James%20Kvaal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fborrowers-repaying-student-loan-debt-before-payments-resume-2023-9%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20reporters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20department%20expects%20borrowers%20to%20flood%20the%20system%20next%20month%2C%20saying%20that%20more%20than%2028%20million%20people%20will%20once%20again%20owe%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20five%20times%20more%20than%20we%20typically%20have%20for%20repayment%20in%20an%20entire%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Kvaal%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20anxiety%20out%20there.%20And%20some%20borrowers%20have%20already%20begun%20making%20payments.%20In%20other%20cases%2C%20there%20will%20be%20borrowers%20who%20will%20take%20some%20time%20to%20work%20student%20loans%20back%20into%20their%20household%20budgets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-companies-not-prepared-for-debt-repayment-gao-foxx-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695244121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e65233912f290019a9d803%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-companies-not-prepared-for-debt-repayment-gao-foxx-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rep.%20Virginia%20Foxx%20and%20Sen.%20Bill%20Cassidy%20asked%20the%20GAO%20to%20investigate%20how%20the%20Education%20Department%20is%20preparing%20student-loan%20companies%20for%20repayment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-companies-not-prepared-for-debt-repayment-gao-foxx-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU