%80%94%20of%20sorts.%20Yet%20not.%20Algeria%20is%20a%20top%20client%20for%20Russian%20exports%2C%20and%20critically%20%E2%80%94%20has%20hundreds%20of%20tanks%20and%20kits%2Fspare%20parts%2C%26quot%3B%20Dara%20Massicot%2C%20a%20senior%20policy%20researcher%20who%20focuses%20on%20Russian%20security%20issues%20at%20the%20California-based%20RAND%20Corporation%20think%20tank%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMassDara%2Fstatus%2F1702757520698126695%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%2C%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20formally%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comments%20came%20in%20response%20to%20an%20earlier%20post%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJack_Mrgln%2Fstatus%2F1702720515125793036%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseveral%20photos%3C%2Fa%3E%20appearing%20to%20show%20Surovikin.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22undefined%5C%22%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%94Jack%20Margolin%20(%40Jack_Mrgln)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1702720515125793036%5C%22%3ESeptember%2015%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20(ISW)%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20think%20tank%2C%20noted%20Surovikin's%20apparent%20presence%20in%20Algeria%20as%20part%20of%20a%20Friday%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Frussian-offensive-campaign-assessment-september-15-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassessment%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Russia's%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20experts%20cited%20several%20additional%20photographs%20of%20Surovikin%20purportedly%20in%20Algeria%2C%20which%20were%20published%20to%20Telegram%20by%20Russian%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20was%20unable%20to%20independently%20verify%20any%20of%20the%20recent%20photographs%20of%20Surovikin%20shared%20to%20X%20and%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20ISW%20assessment%2C%20Surovikin%20had%20previously%20been%20tasked%20with%20a%20leadership%20role%20within%20Commonwealth%20of%20Independent%20States%20(CIS)%2C%20which%20consists%20of%20Russia%20and%20several%20former%20Soviet%20states.%C2%A0ISW%20experts%20noted%20in%C2%A0an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iswresearch.org%2F2023%2F09%2Frussian-offensive-campaign-assessment_10.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month%20the%20move%20%26quot%3Bis%20consistent%20with%20previous%20patterns%20of%20the%20Russian%20military%20leadership%20shifting%20disgraced%20and%20ineffective%20commanders%20to%20peripheral%20positions%20far%20removed%20from%20Ukraine%20without%20discharging%20them%20from%20the%20Russian%20military%20entirely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Wagner%20Group's%20short-lived%20uprising%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20more%20recent%20confirmed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwagner-group-yevgeny-prigozhin-russian-plane-crash-state-media-2023-8%5C%22%3Edeath%20of%20its%20leader%3C%2Fa%3E%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin%20%E2%80%94%20Russia%20has%20moved%20to%20assume%20more%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F09%2F18%2Fwagner-central-african-republic-touadera%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoversight%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20mercenaries'%20activity%20in%20Africa%2C%20where%20they%20had%20long%20acted%20as%20shadowy%20extensions%20of%20Moscow's%20foreign%20policy%20apparatus.%20Surovikin's%20new%20role%2C%20and%20his%20recent%20appearance%20in%20Algeria%2C%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20reflection%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20defense%20ministry%20%26quot%3Bcontinues%20efforts%20to%20assume%20control%20over%20the%20Wagner%20Group's%20operations%20in%20North%20Africa%20and%20may%20have%20assigned%26quot%3B%20Surovikin%20to%20the%20job%2C%20the%20ISW%20experts%20wrote%20in%20their%20Friday%20analysis.%20They%20cited%20Kommersant%2C%20a%20Russian%20news%20outlet%2C%20in%20reporting%20that%20a%20source%20close%20to%20Surovikin%20asserted%20that%20the%20trip%20to%20Algeria%20could%20be%20connected%20to%20his%20%26quot%3Bpossible%20appointment%20to%20oversee%20unspecified%20operations%20in%20Africa.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Commander%20of%20Russia's%20Aerospace%20Forces%20Sergei%20Surovikin%2C%20Chief%20of%20the%20General%20Staff%20of%20the%20Russian%20Armed%20Forces%20Valery%20Gerasimov%20and%20Head%20of%20the%20Main%20Operational%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces'%20General%20Staff%20Sergei%20Rudskoi%20attend%20a%20meeting%20with%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20in%20Sochi%2C%20Russia%2C%20November%203%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6470e3e8085acb0018feac4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECommander%20of%20Russia's%20Aerospace%20Forces%20Sergei%20Surovikin%2C%20Chief%20of%20the%20General%20Staff%20of%20the%20Russian%20Armed%20Forces%20Valery%20Gerasimov%20and%20Head%20of%20the%20Main%20Operational%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces'%20General%20Staff%20Sergei%20Rudskoi%20attend%20a%20meeting%20with%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20in%20Sochi%2C%20Russia%2C%20November%203%2C%202021.%3Cp%3ESputnik%2FMikhail%20Metzel%2FPool%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSurovikin%20may%20be%20involved%20in%20Russian%20efforts%20to%20subsume%20Wagner%20operations%20due%20to%20his%20affiliation%20with%20Wagner%20and%20his%20command%20experience%2C%20although%20it%20is%20unclear%20if%20the%20Russian%20MoD%20intends%20for%20Surovikin%20to%20ass