y.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Femma-roberts-accused-transphobia-angelica-ross-ahs-1235729856%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Femma-roberts-accused-transphobia-angelica-ross-ahs-1235729856%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ancient%20people%20may%20have%20used%20human%20skulls%20for%20cups%20and%20other%20body%20parts%20for%20tools%2C%20according%20to%20a%20burial%20site%20in%20Spain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223071%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20opening%20of%20Cueva%20de%20los%20Marmoles%20in%20Spain%2C%20which%20is%20dark%20inside%20and%20shows%20greenery%20and%20rocks%20outside%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650a3632bf943d00195c0ccc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20opening%20to%20Cueva%20de%20los%20Marmoles%2C%20where%20many%20prehistoric%20people%20buried%20their%20dead%20for%20millennia.%3Cp%3EJ.C.%20Vera%20Rodr%C3%ADguez%2C%20CC-BY%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EAlmost%206%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20communities%20used%20a%20cave%20in%20Spain%20as%20a%20burial%20place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EResearchers%20looked%20at%20bone%20fragments%20of%2012%20individuals%2C%20some%20of%20which%20had%20scrape%20marks.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ENeolithic%20or%20Bronze%20Age%20people%20may%20have%20used%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fscientists-have-found-one-of-the-worlds-oldest-tattooing-kits-2019-3%5C%22%3Ebones%20as%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbronze-age-cauldrons-show-evidence-what-ancient-feasts-looked-like-2023-8%5C%22%3Eprehistoric%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20Spain's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1001375%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECueva%20de%20los%20Marmoles%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20burial%20place%20for%20their%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20examined%20the%20remains%20of%2012%20individuals%20and%20found%20people%20had%20modified%20some%20of%20the%20bones%2C%20possibly%20to%20use%20as%20tools%20and%20drinking%20vessels.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20bones%20seem%20to%20be%20modified.%20A%20cranium%20looks%20scraped%20clean%2C%20and%20two%20leg%20bone%20fragments%2C%20a%20tibia%20and%20fibula%2C%20appear%20polished%20and%20rounded%20from%20use.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnderstanding%20the%20funerary%20practices%20of%20a%20given%20culture%20is%20essential%2C%20as%20it%20sheds%20light%20on%20a%20very%20significant%20part%20of%20its%20social%20and%20cultural%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20Rafael%20M%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%2C%20a%20researcher%20with%20the%20University%20of%20Cordoba%20in%20Spain%2C%20told%20Insider%20via%20email.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20and%20his%20co-authors%20published%20a%20paper%20about%20the%20modified%20remains%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0291152%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPLOS%20ONE%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20bones%20date%20from%20between%20about%206%2C000%20and%203%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20from%20the%20Neolithic%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farchaeologists-upper-class-bronze-age-man-who-underwent-brain-surgery-2023-2%5C%22%3Ethe%20Bronze%20Age%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20motivations%20behind%20practices%20like%20this%20are%20actually%20very%20hard%20to%20get%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fanthropology.uiowa.edu%2Fpeople%2Fkatina-lillios%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKatina%20Lillios%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20anthropology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Iowa%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20believes%20it%20signifies%20that%20the%20living%20had%20extended%20relationships%20to%20their%20deceased.%20%26quot%3BThey%20continued%20to%20engage%20with%20their%20dead%2C%20and%20so%20this%20tells%20us%20that%20the%20dead%20were%20important%20for%20the%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20skull%20cup%20and%20bone%20tools%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvidence%20of%20bone%20modification%20is%20fairly%20common%20for%20the%20Neolithic%20and%20Bronze%20Ages%20in%20Iberia%20and%20Western%20Europe%2C%20and%20there%20are%20many%20theories%20about%20the%20motivations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20range%20from%20a%20desire%20to%20honor%20the%20remains%20of%20close%20relatives%20or%20community%20members%20in%20ritualized%20actions%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20collecting%20human%20trophies%2C%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20notes%20that%20the%20latter%20option%20is%20unlikely%20because%20they%20didn't%20find%20indications%20of%20violence%20on%20the%20remains.%20The%20researchers%20also%20don't%20think%20there%20are%20enough%20cut%20or%20chop%20marks%20to%20suggest%20cannibalism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20collage%20of%20images%20of%20a%20skull%20cap%20from%20the%20Cueva%20de%20los%20Marmoles%20showing%20how%20people%20modified%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650a36d012dc4f001a16e9c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22877%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScrape%20marks%20on%20the%20skull%20cup%20found%20at%20Cueva%20de%20los%20Marmoles%20indicate%20people%20deliberated%20removed%20flesh.%3Cp%3EZ.%20Laffranchi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20oldest%20skull%20cups%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3040189%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFrom%2520this%2520evidence%2520it%2520is%2Coldest%2520directly%2520dated%2520skull%252Dcups.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edate%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20almost%2015%2C000%20BCE.%20Historical%20accounts%20from%20at%20least%20the%205th%20century%20BCE%20note%20people%20drinking%20from%20human%20skulls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20very%20globular%20shape%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-human-skull-210000-years-old-in-greek-cave-2019-7%5C%22%3Ehuman%20skull%3C%2Fa%3E%20makes%20it%20unmistakable%20from%20that%20of%20other%20animals%2C%20as%20well%20as%20allowing%20it%20to%20be%20transformed%20into%20container%20vessels%2C%20such%20as%20cups%20or%20bowls%2C%26quot%3B%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScraping%20and%20cutting%20of%20these%20bones%20left%20traces%20%26quot%3Bthat%20can%20only%20be%20attributed%20to%20human%20action%2C%26quot%3B%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20said.%20In%20contrast%2C%20gnawing%20animals%20leave%20their%20own%20distinctive%20marks%2C%20Lillios%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20polishing%20of%20the%20leg%20bones%20is%20clear%20under%20a%20microscope%2C%20and%20their%20rounded%20appearance%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20result%20of%20their%20use%20as%20tools%2C%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20said.%20It's%20not%20clear%20what%20kind%20of%20purpose%20they%20served%2C%20but%20Lillios%20suggested%20they%20could%20have%20been%20used%20for%20basket%20making%20or%20weaving.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20believe%20other%20humans%20modified%20the%20bones%20while%20the%20remains%20were%20relatively%20fresh.%20Yet%20people%20may%20not%20have%20put%20the%20bodies%20in%20the%20cave%20immediately.%20The%20paper's%20authors%20note%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20finger%20and%20toe%20bones%20may%20indicate%20the%20remains%20were%20partially%20decomposed%20when%20they%20entered%20the%20cave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20cool%2C%20dark%20cave%20would%20help%20preserve%20the%20remains%2C%20the%20researchers%20put%20the%20modifications%20between%20a%20few%20months%20and%20a%20year%20after%20death.%20%26quot%3BThe%20actions%20of%20fragmenting%20and%20manipulating%20the%20bones%20may%20well%20be%20related%20to%20specific%20ritual%20events%20performed%20inside%20the%20cave%2C%26quot%3B%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECaves%20were%20an%20obvious%20choice%20for%20burial%20sites%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20use%20of%20natural%20caves%20as%20burial%20spaces%20is%20a%20universal%20and%20transcultural%20phenomenon%2C%20recorded%20among%20various%20pre-industrial%20human%20societies%20across%20the%20globe%2C%26quot%3B%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20S%C3%A1nchez%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F40000-year-bone-hints-humans-neanderthals-shared-cave-culture-2023-8%5C%22%3ECaves%20offer%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20elements%2C%20but%20Lillios%20said%20they're%20symbolic%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20often%20viewed%20as%20sort%20of%20passageways%20to%20another%20world%20to%20the%20ancestors%2C%20to%20other%20kinds%20of%20worlds%20that%20are%20seen%20as%20sacred%20liminal%20spaces%2C%20spaces%20that%20are%20somewhere%20in%20between%20the%20land%20and%20the%20living%20and%20the%20land%20of%20the%20ancestors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20paper's%20most%20interesting%20findings%20is%20how%20communities%20used%20the%20cave%20between%20generations.%20Using%20radiocarbon%20dating%20for%20the%20remains%2C%20the%20scientists%20learned%20that%20people%20utilized%20the%20cave%20in%20three%20different%20phases%20between%20about%203%2C800%20BCE%20and%201%2C300%20BCE.%20Sometimes%2C%20roughly%201%2C000%20years%20would%20pass%20between%20uses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221857%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20images%20of%20a%20leg%20bone%20from%20the%20Cueva%20de%20los%20Marmoles%20in%20Spain%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650a3727bf943d0019