ibery%20scandal%20rocked%20the%20country%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20agreed%20to%20reconsider%20its%201998%20judgment%20granting%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20for%20taking%20bribes%20to%20make%20a%20speech%20or%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislatures%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20an%20important%20issue%20having%20a%20significant%20bearing%20on%20%26quot%3Bmorality%20of%20polity%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20top%20court%20referred%20the%20issue%20to%20a%20larger%20seven-judge%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20in%20its%201998%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20verdict%20delivered%20in%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20versus%20CBI%20case%20held%20that%20parliamentarians%20have%20immunity%20under%20the%20Constitution%20against%20criminal%20prosecution%20for%20any%20speech%20made%20and%20the%20vote%20cast%20inside%20the%20House%20as%20per%20Article%20105(2)%20and%20Article%20194(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArticle%20105(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20stipulates%20that%20no%20member%20of%20Parliament%20shall%20be%20liable%20to%20any%20proceedings%20in%20any%20court%20in%20respect%20of%20anything%20said%20or%20any%20vote%20cast%20in%20Parliament%20or%20any%20committee%20thereof.%20A%20similar%20provision%20exists%20for%20MLAs%20under%20Article%20194(2).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20a%20bench%20headed%20by%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20hearing%20an%20appeal%20filed%20by%20Sita%20Soren%20-%20JMM%20MLA%20and%20daughter-in-law%20of%20party%20chief%20Shibu%20Soren.%20Ms%20Soren%2C%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20JMM%20bribery%20scandal%2C%20had%20referred%20to%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20the%20crucial%20question%2C%20noting%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Bwide%20ramification%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20of%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%20public%20importance%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20for%20a%20particular%20candidate%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20election%20in%202012.%20She%20contended%20that%20the%20constitutional%20provision%20granting%20lawmakers%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20be%20applied%20to%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20three-judge%20bench%20had%20then%20said%20it%20would%20revisit%20its%20verdict%20in%20the%20sensational%20JMM%20bribery%20case%20involving%20Shibu%20Soren%2C%20a%20former%20Jharkhand%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20and%20ex-Union%20Minister%2C%20and%20four%20other%20party%20MPs%20who%20had%20accepted%20bribes%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20the%20then%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20government%20in%201993.%20The%20Narasimha%20Rao%20government%2C%20which%20was%20in%20a%20minority%2C%20survived%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%20with%20their%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20registered%20a%20case%20against%20Shibu%20Soren%20and%20four%20other%20JMM%20Lok%20Sabha%20MPs%20but%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20quashed%20it%20citing%20the%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20they%20enjoyed%20under%20Article%20105(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20a%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%20it%20will%20set%20up%20a%20seven-judge%20bench%20to%20examine%20the%20matter%20afresh%20and%20%26quot%3Bstraighten%26quot%3B%20the%20law%20even%20as%20Attorney%20General%20R%20Venkataramani%20opposed%20reconsideration%20of%20the%201998%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20of%20the%20considered%20view%20that%20correctness%20of%20the%20view%20of%20the%20majority%20in%20PV%20(Narasimha%20Rao%20case)%20be%20reconsidered%20by%20a%20bench%20of%20seven%20judges.%20The%20purpose%20of%20Article%20105%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20members%20of%20the%20Parliament%20and%20the%20state%20legislatures%20are%20able%20to%20discharge%20their%20duties%20in%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20freedom%20without%20fear%20of%C2%A0consequences%20that%20may%20follow%20for%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20they%20speak%20or%20exercise%20their%20vote%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20object%20is%20not%20to%20set%20apart%20the%20members%20of%20the%20legislature%20as%20persons%20who%20wield%20higher%20privileges%C2%A0in%20terms%20of%20immunity%20of%20general%20law%20of%20the%20land%20which%20citizens%20of%20the%20land%20do%20not%20possess%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20proceedings%20commenced%20today%20before%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justices%20AS%20Bopanna%2C%20MM%20Sundresh%2C%20JB%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Raju%20Ramachandran%2C%20appearing%20for%20Sita%20Soren%2C%20submitted%20the%20mater%20was%20a%20regular%20criminal%20appeal%20which%20involves%20the%20question%20of%20application%20of%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20case%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVenkataramani%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Centre%2C%20referred%20to%20the%20facts%20of%20Sita%20Soren's%20case%20and%20said%20to%20qualify%20for%20protection%20under%20Article%20194(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20applicable%20to%20MLAs%2C%20a%20bribe%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20for%20proceedings%20for%20business%20or%20function%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B(Shibu)%20Soren%20had%20received%20a%20bribe%20for%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20(for%20voting%20against%20it)%20in%20the%20Parliament.%20There%20is%20nothing%20(in%20Sita%20Soren's%20case)%20to%20do%20with%20the%20business%20of%20the%20House.%20The%20function%20must%20have%20a%20nexus%20with%20the%20legislative%20business%20or%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERebutting%20his%20submission%2C%20the%20bench%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20constitution%20bench%2C%20if%20we%20have%20a%20particular%20issue%20which%20deeply%20affects%20the%20morality%20of%20our%20polity%2C%20shouldn't%20we%20take%20an%20opportunity%20to%20straighten%20the%20law%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20four%20eminent%20counsels%20appearing%20in%20this.%20What%20better%20opportunity%20to%20straighten%20the%20law%3F%20Normally%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20get%20into%20a%20broader%20issue%20of%20law%20where%20you%20may%20not%20feel%20that%20you'd%20get%20the%20correct%20assistance%20because%20then%20the%20entire%20burden%20is%20on%20us.%20Even%20then%20we%20take%20up%20the%20burden%20sometimes.%20But%20here%20you%20have%20squarely%20a%20conflict%20between%20the%20viewpoints...we%20should%20set%20the%20law%20straight%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20PS%20Patwalia%2C%20who%20was%20appointed%20amicus%20curiae%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20stated%20there%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bfractured%26quot%3B%20kind%20of%20concurrence%20in%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20judgment%20which%20necessitated%20that%20the%20matter%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20appearing%20for%20one%20of%20the%20intervenors%2C%20echoed%20the%20views%20of%20the%20amicus%20curiae.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESita%20Soren%20had%20appealed%20against%20the%20Jharkhand%20High%20Court%20order%20of%20February%2017%2C%202014%2C%20refusing%20to%20quash%20a%20criminal%20case%20lodged%20against%20her%20for%20allegedly%20taking%20bribes%20to%20vote%20for%20a%20particular%20candidate%20in%20the%202012%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections.%20The%20CBI%20had%20accused%20her%20of%20accepting%20bribes%20from%20one%20candidate%20and%20voting%20for%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695235320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fgv8pfg28_supreme-court_625x300_04_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-review-1998-judgment-in-bribes-for-speech-votes-case-4408186%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20has%20agreed%20to%20reconsider%20its%201998%20judgment%20granting%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20for%20taking%20bribes%20to%20make%20a%20speech%20or%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislatures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-review-1998-judgment-in-bribes-for-speech-votes-case-4408186%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-review-1998-judgment-in-bribes-for-speech-votes-case-4408186%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-review-1998-judgment-in-bribes-for-speech-votes-case-4408186%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BGovernments%20Run%20Countries%2C%20Not%20Secretaries%26quot%3B%3A%20Amit%20Shah%20vs%20Rahul%20Gandhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECountering%20Congress%20MP%20Rahul%20Gandhi's%20claim%20that%20of%20the%2090%20secretaries%20in%20the%20government%20of%20India%2C%20only%20three%20belong%20to%20the%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBC)%20community%2C%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20that%20it%20is%20the%20government%20that%20runs%20the%20country%2C%20not%20the%20secretaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20my%20colleagues%20(Rahul%20Gandhi)%20was%20saying%20that%20of%20the%20people%20who%20run%20the%20country%2C%20only%20three%20are%20from%20the%20OBC%20category.%20Now%20who%20will%20make%20him%20understand%20that%20it%20is%20the%20government%20that%20runs%20the%20country%2C%20not%20the%20secretaries%2C%26quot%3B%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sharp%20attack%20on%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20those%20claiming%20to%20speak%20for%20OBCs%20should%20know%20that%20it%20is%20the%20BJP%20who%20gave%20an%20OBC%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20Constitution%20says%20that%20the%20policy%20of%20the%20country%20will%20be%20decided%20only%20by%20the%20cabinet%20and%20the%20Parliament.%20You%20(Rahul%20Gandhi)%20are%20not%20here%20to%20listen%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20tell%20you%20that%2029%20per%20cent%20of%20MPs%20in%20our%20party%20belong%20to%20the%20OBC%20community.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20do%20a%20comparison%2C%20just%20come%20to%20us.%20And%20in%20our%20union%20cabinet%2C%20there%20are%2029%20ministers%2C%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20community.%20Out%20of%201358%20MLAs%2C%20there%20are%20365%20MLAs%20in%20our%20party%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20OBC%20category...%20You%20speak%20about%20the%20OBCs%2C%20but%20it%20was%20the%20BJP%20who%20gave%20this%20country%20a%20PM%20from%20the%20OBC%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Amit%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20spoke%20in%20the%20Lower%20House%20just%20before%20Mr%20Shah%20claimed%20that%20there%20are%20only%20three%20secretaries%20in%20the%20government%20of%20India%20from%20the%20OBC%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20shocked%20to%20find%20out%20that%20out%20of%2090%20secretaries%20in%20the%20government%20of%20India%2C%20only%20three%20are%20OBCs.%20These%20secretaries%20only%20control%20five%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20budget.%20If%20the%20country's%20budget%20is%20Rs%2044%20lakh%20crore%20then%20Rs%202.4%20lakh%20crore%20controls%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20concerns%20from%20the%20Opposition%20about%20OBC%20representation%2C%20delimitation%2C%20and%20the%20delay%20in%20implementation%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20the%20bill%20will%20be%20implemented%20soon%20after%20the%20census%20and%20delimitation%20after%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCensus%20and%20delimitation%20exercises%20will%20be%20conducted%20soon%20after%20the%20elections%2C%20and%20women%20will%20have%20a%20greater%20voice%20in%20the%20Parliament%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20questioning%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20previous%20government%20for%20not%20passing%20the%20Bill%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20fifth%20attempt%20to%20bring%20the%20women's%20quota%20bill.%20From%20Devegowda%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20Manmohan%20Singh%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20four%20attempts%20were%20made%20to%20bring%20this%20bill...%20What%20was%20the%20reason%20this%20bill%20was%20not%20passed%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmit%20Shah%20also%20talked%20about%20the%20women-centric%20initiatives%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20introduced%20ever%20since%20it%20took%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen's%20security%2C%20respect%2C%20and%20equal%20participation%20have%20been%20the%20life%20force%20of%20government%20since%20PM%20Modi%20took%20the%20oath%20of%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20enumerating%20schemes%20such%20as%20free%20LPG%20cylinders%2C%20Mahila%20Samman%20Savings%20scheme%2C%20maternity%20leave%20and%20Beti%20Bachao%2C%20Beti%20Padhao%20as%20initiatives%20that%20have%20empowered%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongress%20ruled%20for%20over%20five%20decades%20in%20this%20country%2C%20but%20there%20were%2011%20crore%20families%20who%20were%20deprived%20of%20toilets.%20They%20gave%20the%20'Gareebi%20Hatao'%20slogan%20but%20couldn't%20make%20any%20arrangements%20for%20the%20poor.%20When%20a%20house%20doesn't%20have%20a%20toilet%2C%20then%20the%20most%20affected%20ones%20are%20the%20daughters%2C%20sisters%2C%20and%20mothers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Home%20Minister%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%20will%20ensure%20the%20participation%20of%20women%20in%20decision-making%2C%20and%20policy-making%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20disappointed%20women%20four%20times%20before.%20We%20have%20to%20rise%20above%20politics%20now...%20Today%2C%20I%20want%20to%20urge%20the%20Treasury%20and%20Opposition%20that%20we%20should%20unite%20on%20this%20new%20beginning%20and%20with%20consensus%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20to%20give%20reservation%20to%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20passage%20of%20the%20bill%20will%20mark%20the%20start%20of%20a%20new%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695234480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F3n1mpgmg_amit-shah-lok-sabha-pti-650_650x400_20_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgovernments-run-countries-not-secretaries-amit-shah-vs-rahul-gandhi-4407913%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Countering%20Congress%20MP%20Rahul%20Gandhi's%20claim%20that%20of%20the%2090%20secretaries%20in%20the%20government%20of%20India%2C%20only%20three%20belong%20to%20the%20OBC%20community%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20that%20it%20is%20the%20government%20that%20runs%20the%20country%2C%20not%20the%20secretaries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgovernments-run-countries-not-secretaries-amit-shah-vs-rahul-gandhi-4407913%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meta%20Releases%20Second%20Human%20Rights%20Report%2C%20Activists%20Say%20No%20Concrete%20Plan%20to%20Tackle%20Issues%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F30122835%2FMeta.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20second%20annual%20report%20on%20human%20rights%20by%20social%20media%20giant%20Meta%20has%20once%20again%20come%20under%20criticism%20from%20rights%20activists%20who%20say%20it%20leaves%20several%20questions%20unanswered%2C%20especially%20about%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20demonstrate%20election%20preparedness%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeta%20released%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhumanrights.fb.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F2022-Meta-Human-Rights-Report.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20September%2019%2C%20dedicating%20less%20than%20two%20pages%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20diligence%E2%80%9D%20section%20to%20India%20%E2%80%93%20a%20country%20that%20is%20pivotal%20to%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20growth%20but%20also%20one%20where%20it%20has%20faced%20serious%20allegations%20that%20it%20violated%20its%20own%20policies%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ffacebook-hate-speech-bjp-wall-street-journal%5C%22%3Eprotect%20business%20interests%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20lists%20steps%20it%20has%20taken%20to%20address%20issues%20about%20stakeholder%20engagement%2C%20transparency%20reporting%2C%20expanding%20partnerships%20with%20civil%20society%20and%20content%20moderation.%20The%20report%20also%20has%20a%20few%20lines%20about%20%E2%80%9Censuring%20election%20integrity%E2%80%9D%20for%20upcoming%20state%20and%20general%20elections%20in%20India%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20Meta%20will%20activate%20its%20elections%20operation%20centre%2C%20ensure%20content%20reviewers%20provide%20support%20in%2020%20Indian%20languages%20and%20expand%20independent%20fact-checking%20partners%20from%20seven%20to%2011%2C%20covering%2015%20Indian%20languages.%20It%20also%20promised%20to%20enforce%20political%20ads%20transparency%20and%20work%20closely%20with%20both%20electoral%20authorities%20and%20civil%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeta%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20prevent%20the%20spread%20of%20hate%20speech%20and%20divisive%20content%20on%20its%20platforms%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20Facebook%20%E2%80%93%20in%20India%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20highlighted%20in%20the%20past.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ffacebook-hate-speech-india-politics-muslim-hindu-modi-zuckerberg-11597423346%3Fmod%3Ditp_wsj%26yptr%3Dyahoo%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20said%20in%202020%20that%20Facebook%20did%20not%20act%20against%20the%20posts%20of%20a%20BJP%20MLA%2C%20which%20were%20flagged%20internally%20for%20promoting%20violence%2C%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20ruining%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20ruling%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20internal%20report%20prepared%20by%20Facebook%E2%80%99s%20researchers%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ffacebook-services-spread-religious-hatred-wsj-report%5C%22%3Ebelieved%20to%20have%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20WhatsApp%20was%20awash%20with%20%E2%80%9Crumours%20and%20calls%20to%20violence%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20Delhi%20riots%20of%20February%202020%2C%20with%20some%20users%20saying%20they%20were%20frequently%20subjected%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20large%20amount%20of%20content%20that%20encourages%20conflict%2C%20hatred%20and%20violence%20on%20Facebook%20and%20WhatsApp%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFacebook%20whistleblower%20Frances%20Haugen%2C%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ffacebook-whistleblower-frances-haugen-complaints-sec-hate-speech-misinformation-india%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20said%20that%20company%20officials%20were%20aware%20of%20the%20structural%20factors%20that%20cause%20the%20spread%20of%20hate%20speech%20and%20harmful%20political%20rhetoric%20on%20its%20platform.%20Her%20complaint%20also%20had%20references%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfear-mongering%E2%80%9D%20content%20promoted%20by%20%E2%80%9CRashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20users%2C%20groups%20and%20pages%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20BJP%20IT%20Cell%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20use%20of%20duplicate%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQuestions%20have%20also%20been%20raised%20about%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2022%2F3%2F14%2Fhow-a-reliance-funded-company-boosts-bjps-campaigns-on-facebook%5C%22%3Epolitical%20advertising%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2022%2F3%2F15%2Finside-facebook-and-bjps-world-of-ghost-advertisers%5C%22%3EMeta%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Fails%20to%20inspire%20confidence%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20was%20criticised%20by%20Access%20Now%20as%20failing%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshow%20any%20meaningful%20or%20verifiable%20progress%E2%80%9D%20on%20Meta%CA%BCs%20human%20rights%20harms%20in%20India%20or%20propose%20any%20concrete%20plan%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20digital%20rights%20advocay%20group%20said%20that%20the%20report%20does%20not%20elaborate%20on%20the%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Impact%20Assessment%20(HRIA)%20commissioned%20for%20India%20in%202022.%20Civil%20society%20groups%20have%20repeatedly%20requested%20Meta%20to%20release%20the%20full%20report%2C%20to%20no%20avail.%20The%20company%20previously%20released%20similar%20reports%20for%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20Myanmar%2C%20and%20Indonesia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENamrata%20Maheshwari%2C%20Asia%20Pacific%20policy%20counsel%20at%20Access%20Now%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMeta%20continues%20to%20evade%20responsibility%20by%20not%20releasing%20the%20HRIA%20in%20compliance%20with%20UN%20Guiding%20Principles.%20They%20require%20at%20the%20very%20least%20disclosure%20that%20is%20sufficient%20to%20evaluate%20the%20adequacy%20of%20a%20company%CA%BCs%20response%20to%20the%20human%20rights%20impact.%20Without%20the%20full%20picture%20of%20how%20Meta%CA%BCs%20practices%20and%20policies%20have%20impacted%20human%20rights%20in%20India%20and%20the%20specific%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20in%20the%20HRIA%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%93%20governments%2C%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20and%20individuals%20%E2%80%93%20to%20effectively%20scrutinise%20Meta%CA%BCs%20policies%20and%20assess%20their%20adequacy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccess%20Now%20said%20it%20was%20alarmed%20by%20Meta%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20outline%20a%20clear%20plan%20to%20demonstrate%20election%20preparedness%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CMeta%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20harms%20or%20specific%20issues%20it%20envisages%20for%20elections%20in%20India%2C%20nor%20any%20clear%20and%20structured%20plan%20to%20increase%20meaningful%2C%20inclusive%20engagement%20with%20civil%20society%2C%20and%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20feedback%20will%20be%20incorporated%20to%20mitigate%20harms%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMeta%20cannot%20continue%20to%20profit%20off%20of%20Indians%20in%20disregard%20of%20their%20human%20rights.%20India%CA%BCs%20400%20million%20Facebook%20users%20need%20to%20know%20whether%20Meta%20has%20taken%20any%20action%20to%20correct%20the%20imbalance%20in%20applying%20its%20practices%20and%20policies%2C%20including%20on%20political%20advertising%2C%20fake%20accounts%2C%20and%20hate%20speech%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERaman%20Jit%20Singh%20Chima%2C%20Asia%20Pacific%20policy%20director%20at%20Access%20Now%2C%20added%20that%20the%C2%A0absence%20of%20any%20mention%20of%20specific%20steps%20that%20Meta%20will%20take%20to%20ensure%20election%20preparedness%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20gaping%20hole%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20report.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20report%20does%20not%20inspire%20confidence%20that%20Meta%20has%20any%20concrete%20plan%20to%20meaningfully%20consult%20with%20civil%20society%20in%20an%20inclusive%20and%20sustained%20manner%20to%20more%20effectively%20tackle%20misinformation%2C%20disinformation%2C%20political%20ads%20and%20hate%20speech%2C%20which%20can%20escalate%20tensions%20during%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20called%20on%20Meta%20to%20disclose%20the%20full%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20of%20the%20HRIA%20for%20India%2C%20and%20develop%20and%20release%20its%20plan%20to%20tackle%20election-related%20issues%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695234273000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F30122835%2FMeta.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmeta-second-human-rights-report-india-issues-no-plan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20was%20criticised%20by%20Access%20Now%20as%20failing%20to%20%26quot%3Bshow%20any%20meaningful%20or%20verifiable%20progress%26quot%3B%20on%20Meta%CA%BCs%20human%20rights%20harms%20in%20India%20or%20any%20clear%20proposals%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmeta-second-human-rights-report-india-issues-no-plan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fed%20leaves%20rates%20unchanged%20at%205.25-5.50%25%2C%20sees%20tighter%20policy%20through%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695233622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-09%2F27%2Ffull%2F1632710715-5658.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffed-leaves-rates-unchanged-at-5-25-5-50-sees-tighter-policy-through-2024-123092001528_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20they%20did%20in%20June%2C%20Fed%20policymakers%20at%20the%20median%20still%20see%20the%20central%20bank's%20benchmark%20overnight%20interest%20rate%20peaking%20this%20year%20in%20the%205.50%25-5.75%25%20range%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffed-leaves-rates-unchanged-at-5-25-5-50-sees-tighter-policy-through-2024-123092001528_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fworld-news%2Ffed-leaves-rates-unchanged-at-5-25-5-50-sees-tighter-policy-through-2024-123092001528_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fworld-news%2Ffed-leaves-rates-unchanged-at-5-25-5-50-sees-tighter-policy-through-2024-123092001528_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mumbai%20Woman%20Dies%20After%20SUV%20Hits%20Her.%20Driver%20Misleads%20Cops%2C%20CCTV%20Nails%20Him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20driver%20of%20a%20car%20has%20been%20arrested%20for%20fatally%20knocking%20down%20a%2073-year-old%20woman%20in%20Mumbai%20last%20week%2C%20but%20trying%20to%20pass%20it%20on%20as%20an%20accident%20in%20which%20he%20had%20no%20fault%20and%20where%20he%20in%20fact%20helped%20the%20victim%20by%20taking%20her%20to%20a%20hospital%2C%20police%20said%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20accident%20took%20place%20when%20the%20deceased%2C%20Pushpa%20Dhanaji%20Keni%2C%20was%20crossing%20a%20road%20at%20Sion%20in%20Central%20Mumbai%20for%20going%20to%20a%20temple%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%2C%20identified%20as%20Ismail%20Ansari%2C%20claimed%20the%20woman%20suddenly%20collapsed%20while%20crossing%20the%20road%20and%20fell%20in%20front%20of%20his%20SUV%20on%20September%2010%2C%20an%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20driver's%20fault%20in%20the%20accident%20was%20established%20with%20the%20help%20of%20CCTV%20footage%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20hitting%20Keni%20with%20his%20car%2C%20Ansari%20made%20a%20call%20from%20her%20mobile%20phone%20to%20her%20daughter%2C%20who%20works%20in%20the%20Central%20Railway%20as%20a%20head%20booking%20clerk%2C%20informing%20she%20fell%20on%20the%20road%20after%20experiencing%20dizziness%20and%20that%20he%20was%20taking%20her%20to%20Sion%20Hospital%20for%20treatment%2C%20the%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20car%20driver%20also%20asked%20the%20woman's%20daughter%20to%20come%20to%20the%20hospital.%20The%20elderly%20woman's%20daughter%20visited