nsparent%20about%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20interference%E2%80%9D%20from%20China%20and%20its%20secrecy%20over%20national%20security%20matters%2C%20newspapers%20in%20the%20country%20analysed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20unprecedented%20move%2C%20Trudeau%20said%20that%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%20allegations%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%20being%20behind%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20who%20was%20accused%20of%20being%20a%20pro-Khalistan%20terrorist%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20this%20year%2C%20Trudeau%20and%20his%20team%20erred%20on%20the%20side%20of%20secrecy.%20For%20the%20last%20few%20months%20of%20this%20year%2C%20it%20appears%20they%E2%80%99ve%20decided%20to%20risk%20erring%20on%20the%20side%20of%20transparency%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestar.com%2Fpolitics%2Fpolitical-opinion%2Fhere-s-why-justin-trudeau-went-public-with-an-explosive-allegation-against-india%2Farticle_0eac7d09-3ca7-5924-9c12-f2ce8e54a7e8.html%5C%22%3Eanalysed%20%3Cem%3EToronto%20Star%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20Susan%20Delacourt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20Trudeau%20government%20was%20looking%20to%20avoid%20a%20rerun%20of%20its%20travails%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20this%20year%2C%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20government%20was%20battered%20by%20a%20constant%20barrage%20of%20media%20stories%20about%20foreign%20interference%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20revolving%20around%20China.%20Some%20of%20them%20were%20single-sourced%3B%20some%20were%20problematic%2C%20according%20to%20the%20initial%20(and%20ill-fated)%20report%20from%20special%20rapporteur%20David%20Johnston.%20Yet%20in%20every%20case%2C%20Trudeau%20and%20his%20team%20seemed%20incapable%20of%20saying%20anything%20beyond%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20took%20the%20issue%20seriously.%20They%20were%20starting%20to%20look%20at%20best%20flat-footed%2C%20at%20worst%20incompetent%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote%20in%20the%20opinion%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fexercise-utmost-caution-india-issues-advisory-for-those-considering-travel-to-canada%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Exercise%20Utmost%20Caution%E2%80%99%3A%20India%20Issues%20Advisory%20for%20Those%20Considering%20Travel%20to%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Canadian%20National%20Security%20Advisor%2C%20Jody%20Thomas%2C%20had%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20the%20government%20was%20taking%20a%20hard%20look%20at%20whether%20secrecy%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctoo%20excessive%E2%80%9D%20around%20the%20matter%20of%20foreign%20interference.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20were%20all%20signs%20that%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20government%20was%20starting%20to%20see%20hyper-security%20around%20intelligence%20as%20a%20political%20liability.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20referred%20to%20Trudeau%20as%20telling%20reporters%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20Canadians%20%E2%80%9Chave%20a%20right%20to%20know%20and%20need%20to%20know%20when%20things%20are%20going%20on%20like%20this%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20we%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20do%20this%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20newspaper%20%3Ci%3EGlobe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fi%3E%20published%20a%20column%20by%20Indian%20strategic%20analyst%20Brahma%20Chellaney%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fopinion%2Farticle-justin-trudeau-brings-canadas-ties-with-india-under-increasing-strain%2F%5C%22%3Equestioned%20the%20haste%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20which%20Trudeau%20has%20gone%20public%20with%20the%20allegations%20despite%20the%20investigations%20not%20being%20complete.%20He%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CA%20wiser%20approach%20would%20have%20been%20to%20charge%20all%20the%20suspects%20and%20present%20evidence%20of%20any%20Indian%20government%20involvement%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law.%20But%20with%20no%20arrests%2C%20let%20alone%20evidence%2C%20Mr.%20Trudeau%20has%20dealt%20a%20major%20blow%20to%20Ottawa%E2%80%99s%20bilateral%20relationship%20with%20New%20Delhi%20by%20echoing%20the%20allegations%20of%20Canadian%20Sikh%20extremists%20who%20have%20held%20India%20responsible%20from%20the%20day%20Mr.%20Nijjar%20was%20shot.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChellaney%20pointed%20out%20that%20India%20has%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20been%20accused%20of%20carrying%20out%20an%20assassination%20on%20Western%20soil%2C%20even%20though%20it%20has%20long%20been%20the%20target%20of%20major%20international%20terrorist%20attacks%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20about%20the%20operations%20of%20Sikh%20and%20Kashmiri%20terrorists%20from%20Anglosphere%20countries%20go%20back%20to%20the%201980s%2C%20when%20an%20Indian%20diplomat%20was%20murdered%20in%20Birmingham%20in%20Britain%20and%20a%20bomb%20downed%20an%20Air%20India%20flight%20from%20Toronto%2C%20killing%20all%20329%20people%20on%20board%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20%3Ci%3EGlobe%3C%2Fi%3E%20columnist%2C%20Andrew%20Coyne%2C%20said%20that%20India%20may%20have%20had%20%E2%80%9Cample%20reason%20over%20the%20years%20to%20be%20annoyed%20by%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20indulgence%20of%20Sikh%20separatists%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20Sikh%20terrorists%2C%20in%20particular%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fopinion%2Farticle-did-india-assassinate-a-canadian-citizen%2F%5C%22%3Eargument%20was%20%E2%80%9Cirrelevant%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20current%20allegations.%20%E2%80%9CRegardless%20of%20whether%20Mr.%20Nijjar%20was%20merely%20a%20Sikh%20separatist%20or%2C%20as%20India%20maintains%2C%20a%20terrorist%2C%20he%20was%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20and%20entitled%20to%20the%20protections%20of%20Canadian%20law.%20The%20government%20of%20India%20had%20no%20right%20to%20kill%20him%2C%20or%20to%20do%20harm%20to%20him%20of%20any%20kind%20%E2%80%93%20not%20in%20India%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20in%20Canada.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnot-trying-to-provoke-trudeau-india-nijjar-matter-seriously%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Not%20Trying%20to%20Provoke%E2%80%99%3A%20Trudeau%20Asks%20India%20to%20Take%20Nijjar%20Matter%20Seriously%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECoyne%20wrote%20that%20the%20issue%20was%20not%20about%20sympathy%20for%20Nijjar%20or%20his%20aims%2C%20but%20about%20the%20obligation%20of%20national%20governments%20to%20act%20within%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20now%2C%20the%20onus%20is%20on%20the%20government%20of%20India%20to%20cooperate%20fully%20in%20the%20investigation%20of%20Mr.%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing.%20At%20the%20least%20it%20could%20do%20Canada%20the%20courtesy%20of%20officially%20deploring%20it%2C%20as%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20demanded.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFormer%20head%20of%20the%20Canadian%20Intelligence%20Service%20Richard%20Fadden%2C%20who%20also%20served%20as%20the%20national%20security%20adviser%20to%20Trudeau%20and%20his%20predecessor%20Stephen%20Harper%2C%20told%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Globe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fi%3E%20that%20Canada%20should%20suspend%20intelligence-sharing%20or%20cooperation%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Canada%20should%20prepare%20for%20a%20long%20period%20of%20chilly%20relations%20with%20India%20but%20should%20also%20attempt%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20ensure%20New%20Delhi%20never%20does%20something%20like%20this%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20there%20was%20some%20anxiety%20in%20the%20Canadian%20media%20that%20the%20US%20was%20not%20coming%20as%20strongly%20as%20expected%20on%20behalf%20of%20its%20closest%20neighbour%2C%20but%20was%20perceived%20to%20be%20more%20neutral%20and%20not%20taking%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F09%2F19%2Findia-expels-canada-diplomat-sikh-assassination%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%E2%80%99%3C%2Fi%3Es%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20claimed%20that%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20for%20a%20joint%20statement%20by%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20intelligence%20sharing%20alliance%20was%20rebuffed%20was%20widely%20reported%2C%20which%20led%20to%20a%20formal%20denial%20from%20the%20Canadian%20foreign%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETerming%20the%20report%20as%20false%2C%20Ottawa%20said%20that%20Canada%20had%20only%20briefed%20its%20allies.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20claim%20reported%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Canada%20asked%20Allies%20to%20publicly%20condemn%20the%20murder%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20and%20were%20subsequently%20rebuffed%2C%20is%20false%2C%E2%80%9D%20Emily%20Williams%2C%20press%20secretary%20to%20Canadian%20Foreign%20Affairs%20Minister%20M%C3%A9lanie%20Joly%2C%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fpolitics%2Farticle-conservative-leader-pierre-poilievre-urges-pm-trudeau-to-reveal%2F%5C%22%3Ean%20e-mailed%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fcanada-worked-closely-with-us-indias-possible-link-killing-source-2023-09-19%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EReuters%20%3C%2Fi%3Ealso%20quoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Canadian%20%E2%80%9Csource%E2%80%9D%20as%20saying%20that%20Ottawa%20%E2%80%9Chad%20been%20working%20with%20the%20US%20very%20closely%2C%20including%20on%20the%20public%20disclosure%20yesterday%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20public%20broadcaster%20reported%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Csenior%20US%20administration%20official%20reached%20out%20to%20CBC%20News%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fcanada-india-nijjar-sikh-trudeau-modi-1.6971670%5C%22%3Edispute%20that%20characterisation%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReports%20that%20Canada%20asked%20the%20US%20to%20publicly%20condemn%20the%20murder%20and%20that%20we%20refused%20are%20false%20and%20we%20would%20strongly%20push%20back%20on%20the%20rumours%20that%20we%20were%20reluctant%20to%20speak%20publicly%20about%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20we%20very%20clearly%20and%20very%20publicly%20have%20done%20the%20opposite%20by%20expressing%20deep%20concern%20shortly%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Trudeau%20made%20the%20announcement%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20anonymous%20US%20official%20told%20CBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20former%20Canadian%20national%20security%20analyst%20and%20an%20international%20relations%20professor%2C%20Stephanie%20Carvin%2C%20said%20that%20Canada%20should%20not%20expect%20strong%20rallying%20support%20from%20allies%20in%20the%20same%20way%20it%20was%20roundly%20backed%20during%20its%20campaign%20against%20China%E2%80%99s%20jailing%20of%20two%20Canadian%20nationals%20by%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20a%20much%20harder%20case%2C%20because%20everyone%E2%80%99s%20trying%20to%20woo%20India%20right%20now.%20And%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20risk%20upsetting%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20you%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20is%20useful%20%5Bin%5D%20countering%20China%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20not.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnalysing%20the%20US%20comment%2C%20Carvin%20said%20it%20backed%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20version%20of%20events%20but%20was%20muted%20in%20its%20criticism%20against%20India.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20that%20this%20is%20the%20best%20we%20could%20probably%20hope%20for%20in%20this%20situation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695220207000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20184825%2Fimage-1329.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadian-media-trudeau-public-a