n-say-scientists-12965544%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20world's%20foulest-smelling%20flower%20-%20which%20mimics%20the%20odour%20of%20rotting%20flesh%20-%20could%20be%20at%20risk%20of%20extinction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fworlds-biggest-flower-that-stinks-like-rotten-meat-at-risk-of-extinction-say-scientists-12965544%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fworlds-biggest-flower-that-stinks-like-rotten-meat-at-risk-of-extinction-say-scientists-12965544%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fworlds-biggest-flower-that-stinks-like-rotten-meat-at-risk-of-extinction-say-scientists-12965544%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Said%20While%20Acquitting%20Four%20People%20Convicted%20of%20Dacoity%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F18141040%2FInside_the_Supreme_Court_of_India._02.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20case%20involving%20six%20people%20who%20were%20convicted%20on%20the%20testimony%20of%20two%20constables%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20acquitted%20three%20of%20them%20last%20week%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20had%20acquitted%20the%20other%20three%20five%20years%20ago%20after%20entirely%20rejecting%20the%20constables%E2%80%99%20testimony.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20similar%20or%20identical%20evidence%20of%20eyewitnesses%20against%20two%20accused%20by%20ascribing%20them%20the%20same%20or%20similar%20role%2C%20the%20Court%20cannot%20convict%20one%20accused%20and%20acquit%20the%20other%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Abhay%20Oka%20and%20Sanjay%20Karol%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2019%2F18308%2F18308_2019_9_1502_46809_Judgement_13-Sep-2023.pdf%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20September%2013%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20six%20people%20were%20convicted%20by%20a%20Gujarat%20trial%20court%20in%20March%202006%20of%20committing%20offences%20including%20dacoity%20and%20murder%20during%20an%20incident%20of%20mob%20violence%20in%20Ahmedabad%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20some%20of%20them%20were%20sentenced%20to%20life%20in%20prison%2C%20but%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20reduced%20this%20to%2010%20years%20in%202016%2C%20the%20order%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20same%20year%2C%20three%20of%20the%20six%20convicts%20had%20appealed%20against%20their%20sentence%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20the%20court%20acquitted%20them%2C%20and%20entirely%20rejected%20the%20testimony%20of%20the%20two%20constables%20on%20which%20their%20sentence%20was%20solely%20based.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20fourth%20convict%2C%20who%20his%20counsel%20said%20was%20also%20sentenced%20solely%20on%20the%20constables%E2%80%99%20testimony%2C%20filed%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018%2C%20but%20was%20summarily%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20that%20he%20must%20also%20be%20acquitted%2C%20as%20his%20case%20stood%20on%20the%20same%20footing%20as%20that%20of%20the%20three%20who%20were%20acquitted%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20accused%20%E2%80%A6%20must%20get%20the%20benefit%20of%20parity%20%E2%80%A6%20If%20we%20fail%20to%20grant%20relief%20to%20%5Bhim%5D%2C%20the%20rights%20guaranteed%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20will%20be%20violated.%20It%20will%20amount%20to%20doing%20manifest%20injustice%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArticle%2021%20relates%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20life%20and%20liberty.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20we%20will%20have%20to%20recall%20the%20order%20passed%20in%20the%20special%20leave%20petition%20filed%20by%20%5Bthe%20accused%5D%E2%80%9D%2C%20its%20order%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20two%20of%20the%20six%20convicts%20who%20were%20acquitted%20by%20the%20top%20court%20between%202018%20and%20last%20week.%20These%20two%20did%20not%20appeal%20against%20their%20sentence%2C%20but%20the%20court%20acquitted%20them%20anyway%2C%20as%20they%20were%20accused%20of%20playing%20similar%20roles%20based%20on%20identical%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20manner%20of%20doubt%20that%20the%20benefit%20which%20is%20granted%20to%20%5Bthe%20accused%20who%20were%20acquitted%20in%202018%5D%20deserves%20to%20be%20extended%20to%20%5Bthe%20present%20two%20accused%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Esuo%20motu%3C%2Fem%3E%20exercise%20of%20powers%20under%20Article%20136%20is%20warranted%20as%20it%20is%20a%20question%20of%20the%20liberty%20of%20the%20said%20two%20accused%20guaranteed%20by%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustices%20Oka%20and%20Karol%20had%20earlier%20pointed%20out%20that%20this%C2%A0%3Cem%3Esuo%20motu%3C%2Fem%3E%20power%20was%20only%20to%20be%20exercised%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Crarest%20of%20the%20rare%20cases%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20case%20was%20the%20bench%20hearing%20in%20the%20first%20place%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20made%20these%20decisions%20while%20hearing%20an%20appeal%20by%20a%20seventh%20accused%20named%20Javed%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Qureshi%2C%20who%20was%20convicted%20along%20with%20the%20previous%20six%2C%20but%20whose%20conviction%20was%20based%20on%20a%20different%20testimony.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20named%20Gitaben%20Bhailal%20said%20Qureshi%20was%20part%20of%20the%20mob%20in%202003%20and%20had%20snatched%20her%20necklace%20during%20the%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20bench%20noted%20that%20only%20Bhailal%20had%20identified%20Qureshi%2C%20that%20she%20did%20not%20know%20him%20beforehand%2C%20that%20he%20was%20not%20produced%20in%20a%20police%20identification%20parade%2C%20and%20that%20Bhailal%20had%20identified%20him%20in%20the%20trial%20court%20around%20two%20years%20after%20his%20alleged%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20accept%20that%20in%20such%20a%20large%20mob%20gathered%20around%20%5BBhailal%5D%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20witness%20could%20remember%20the%20face%20of%20only%20one%20accused%20and%20recognise%20him%20after%20a%20lapse%20of%20about%20two%20years%20from%20the%20date%20of%20the%20incident%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20there%20was%20neither%20any%20direct%20nor%20circumstantial%20evidence%20to%20corroborate%20Bhailal%E2%80%99s%20accusation%20against%20Qureshi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20a%20corroboration%20is%20completely%20absent%20in%20this%20case.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20conviction%20of%20the%20appellant%20cannot%20be%20sustained%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%2013%20people%20were%20prosecuted%20in%20this%20case.%20Seven%20were%20convicted%20and%20sentenced.%20Four%20were%20acquitted%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20September%2013%20this%20year%2C%20and%20three%20were%20acquitted%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695206709000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F18141040%2FInside_the_Supreme_Court_of_India._02.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fif-people-accused-of-similar-role-based-on-same-evidence-cannot-convict-some-not-others-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20four%20were%20accused%20of%20being%20part%20of%20a%20violent%20mob%20in%20Ahmedabad%2020%20years%20ago%20which%20killed%20at%20least%20one%20person.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fif-people-accused-of-similar-role-based-on-same-evidence-cannot-convict-some-not-others-supre